We've been in Harlem for almost four years and have yet to find a great taco place until tonight. The website was beautifully designed but from the looks of it we thought we were going to walk into a much "fancier" place. The place looked more HK on the website but what we got was Spanish Harlem - and this is exactly what we wanted. I was very skeptical because the place seemed a Mexican restaurant but it had mashed potatoes and hamburgers on the menu which is usually never a good sign. NOW in short the service was fast and amazing. Nice and not too sweet margaritas, delicious guac served with salsa and the tacos (chicken and shrimp) were both fantastic. Usually the chicken is super dried out and the shrimp overcooked but this was not the case at all. Both seemed cooked to order. Only two desserts on the menu and we tried them both which were great. Only complaints were that the ice cream seemed freezer burned a bit. Very frosty and not creamy and I wished that there would have been a different sauce served with one of the desserts. The caramel sauce was great but something different would have been better for the crepes. Overall a great experience that will definitely bring us back! Of course consistency is the key for us so I hope that when we go back everything is just as good. Thanks La Avenida!
